news.title: Spain is considering a 100% tax on homes bought by foreigners
news.para: Spanish Prime Minister Pedro Sanchez announced the plan this week to tackle housing affordability and high rents in the Southern European nation. He said that the overall goal was to provide "more housing, better regulation and greater aid."

news.title: Sundaram Alternates raises over Rs 1,000 crore for SA RE Credit Fund IV
news.para: The SA RE Credit Fund IV will focus primarily on South Indian micro markets with established developers. The fund is 70% deployed in a portfolio that is yielding close to 19% IRRs.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government plans to revive scheme to regularize encroached house sites
news.para: Sources said that chief minister Chandrababu Naidu has decided to regularize house-sites of the poor who encroached govt lands.

news.title: J&K CM urges officers to adopt urban-planning strategies for planned development
news.para: Abdullah was speaking at a meeting convened here to review and discuss the implementation of proposed urban-planning schemes and policies aimed at transforming the Union Territory's urban landscape to bring about planned development.

news.title: Special drive in South Goa to act against illegal constructions
news.para: The initiative aims to streamline the disposal of cases by bringing together applicants and key department representatives under one roof.

news.title: Every poor person in the country will have a permanent house: Madhya Pradesh CM
news.para: Referring to an old survey in Madhya Pradesh, he said that permanent houses are to be provided to 16 lakh beneficiaries and the state has got 8.5 lakh new houses as of now.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Builder fined for illegally trimming seven trees in Chandkheda
news.para: A video that went viral showed the top branches of seven trees being cut at Zanzar Sky construction site in Chandkheda on Jan 12, prompting a team from the Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation to visit the site the next day.

news.title: Architects are bringing nature home by making trees part of the plan
news.para: Some architects and home designers are using one particular biophilic element to striking effect: trees.

news.title: Telangana: Fire department proposes amendment to mandate NOC for all commercial buildings
news.para: At present, such commercial structures below 15 metres are not regulated under the Act and do not need an NOC.

news.title: DTCP issues 300 more notices for illegal construction in Gurugram's DLF 3
news.para: Notices are being systematically pasted on the properties, with 1,100 notices already displayed to ensure compliance with zoning regulations.

news.title: Los Angeles rental hits $40,000 per month as fires disrupt housing market
news.para: Incoming calls at LA Estate Rentals, which manages and leases homes in some of the area’s costliest neighbourhoods, have jumped to 500 a day, more than 10 times the number before the fires, said owner Patrick Michael.

news.title: UK's Vistry warns of uncertain market conditions
news.para: Vistry, which has issued three profit warnings since last October, reaffirmed its forecast for 2024 adjusted pre-tax profit at about 250 million pounds ($305.1 million).

news.title: House prices in UK rise by most since February 2023
news.para: Average house prices rose by 3.3% in the 12 months to November - the fastest increase since February 2023 - after a downwardly revised 3.0% increase in October, the Office for National Statistics said.

news.title: India's infra-driven economy will lead to CAGR growth of 7-8% in cement demand: Report
news.para: The report stated that after a brief slowdown anticipated in FY25E, the sector is expected to witness strong growth, driven by positive demand fundamentals and structural changes within the industry.

news.title: Spain's housing shares inch up after government measures
news.para: Shares of Neinor Homes, Aedas Homes, Metrovacesa and Inmocemento all took a hit on Monday after Spanish Prime Minister Pedro Sanchez announced a plan to raise taxes on holiday rentals and set a tax of up to 100% on purchases of houses by non-European Union foreigners living abroad.

news.title: Odisha mines minister helps seize 20 trucks for ferrying sand illegally
news.para: The minister, who was returning from performing rituals at the Nilamadhab temple during the deity's Pushyabhishek, noticed several trucks transporting sand from the Mahanadi river bed.

news.title: UK'S Persimmon sees 2024 profit at top end of market view
news.para: Shares in the FTSE 100 builder rose about 4.5% to 1,104 pence in early trade, lifting the broader housing index , with most of its blue-chip peers gaining around 3%.
